{
  "text": "Tang et al. synthesized YF3: Yb 3+ Er 3+ upconverting particles (UCPs) using the hydrothermal method. The structure of MIPs@UCPs is presented in Figure 5 , which demonstrates that the In recent years, MIFs based on carbon QDs [CITATION_1] , graphene QDs [CITATION_2] , and C 3 N 4 QDs [CITATION_3] have been developed. These fluorescence sensors overcome the problem of toxic elements overflowing from the semiconductor quantum dots. They are also eco-friendly and generate a strong fluorescence signal [CITATION_4] . Liu et al. ",
